OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776564202
OL,3,CIran closes Strait of Hormuz again in
OL,4,Cresponse to US blockade on its ports
OL,6,FAs recently as Friday, Iranian foreign
OL,7,Fminister Abbas Araghchi said that in
OL,8,Fline with a ceasefire agreement
OL,9,Fbetween Israel and Lebanon, the Strait
OL,10,Fof Hormuz was "completely open" for
OL,11,Fall commercial vessels.
OL,13,FSpeaking at an event that evening,
OL,14,FTrump said said that while the strait
OL,15,Fwas "fully open and ready for full
OL,16,Fpassage", the US would "have to finish
OL,17,Fthe deal before we open it for Iran".
OL,26,@wD@EOUxD@HO]xD@XOUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776564202
OL,3,CIran closes Strait of Hormuz again in
OL,4,Cresponse to US blockade on its ports
OL,6,FThis appeared to present a red line
OL,7,Ffor Tehran, with top Iranian officials
OL,8,Fclaiming the US blockade violated a
OL,9,Ffragile ceasefire agreement between
OL,10,Fthe two countries.
OL,12,FEarly on Saturday, Iran's
OL,13,Fparliamentary speaker Mohammad Bagher
OL,14,FQalibaf posted on X that if the US
OL,15,Fblockade continued "the Strait of
OL,16,FHormuz will not remain open".
OL,18,FMeanwhile data firm Kpler said
OL,19,Fmovement through the strait remained
OL,20,Fconfined to corridors requiring Iran's
OL,21,Fapproval.
OL,26,@wD@TOUxD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776564202
OL,3,CIran closes Strait of Hormuz again in
OL,4,Cresponse to US blockade on its ports
OL,6,FThe US and Iran are in the middle of a
OL,7,Ffragile truce which is due to last
OL,8,Funtil April 22, while Israel and
OL,9,FLebanon have begun a 10-day ceasefire.
OL,11,FAsked by a reporter on Friday night
OL,12,Fwhat he will do if there's no deal
OL,13,Fwhen a ceasefire with Iran expires
OL,14,Fnext week, Trump said: "I don't know.
OL,15,FMaybe I won't extend it, but the
OL,16,Fblockade is going to remain.
OL,18,F"But maybe I won't extend it, so
OL,19,Fyou'll have a blockade and
OL,20,Funfortunately we'll have to start
OL,21,Fdropping bombs again."
OL,26,@vD@XOUzD@AOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1776564202
OL,3,CIran closes Strait of Hormuz again in
OL,4,Cresponse to US blockade on its ports
OL,6,FHowever, Trump also told reporters
OL,7,Faccompanying him aboard Air Force One
OL,8,Fto Washington that, "I think it's
OL,9,Fgoing to happen," referring to a deal.
OL,11,FDespite the escalation in the Strait
OL,12,Fof Hormuz, officials in Pakistan, who
OL,13,Fhelped broker the current truce, say
OL,14,Fthe United States and Iran are still
OL,15,Fmoving closer to a deal ahead of the
OL,16,FApril 22 ceasefire deadline.
OL,26,@pD@UOUqD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
